
this is a script that controls the order of the ethernet interfaces on a linux 
box. it can either set up interfaces based on a list of hardware addresses or based on the PCI bus id.

it's being used on systems with multiple interfaces, a static /dev and monolithic kernels.

Author:  Petre Rodan <2b4eda@subdimension.ro>
Date:    2012 03 31
License: GPLv3
URL:     github.com/rodan/fix_eth_order 
dependencies: iproute2-2.6.36 or newer


